This paper deals with routing in wireless networks, which is a topic that falls under the category of computer networks (cs.NI). The paper also discusses algorithms and distributed computing, which are subfields of computer science that fall under the categories of distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC) and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). The paper also discusses information theory (cs.IT) in the context of constructing a generalized t-spanner for CDC-path. Finally, the paper discusses the use of directional antennas, which is a topic that falls under the category of signal processing (cs.SI).
